ACCOUNTS RECEIVABLE AS OF

DECEMBER 31, 2013

, INCLUDED

$112

OF UNBILLABLE RECEIVABLES ON A LONG-TERM CONTRACT WITH LIGHTSQUARED, LLC (LIGHTSQUARED) RELATED TO THE CONSTRUCTION OF

TWO

COMMERCIAL SATELLITES. ONE OF THE SATELLITES HAS BEEN DELIVERED, AND THE OTHER IS SUBSTANTIALLY COMPLETE BUT REMAINS IN BOEING’S POSSESSION. ON MAY 14, 2012, LIGHTSQUARED FILED FOR CHAPTER 11 BANKRUPTCY PROTECTION. WE BELIEVE THAT OUR RIGHTS IN THE SECOND SATELLITE AND RELATED GROUND-SEGMENT ASSETS ARE SUFFICIENT TO PROTECT THE VALUE OF OUR R

ECEIVABLES IN THE EVENT LIGHTSQUARED FAILS TO MAKE PAYMENTS AS CONTRACTUALLY REQUIRED OR REJECTS ITS CONTRACT WITH US. GIVEN THE UNCERTAINTIES INHERENT IN BANKRUPTCY PROCEEDINGS, IT IS REASONABLY POSSIBLE THAT WE COULD INCUR LOSSES RELATED TO THESE RECEIVABLES IN CONNECTION WITH THE LIGHTSQUARED BANKRUPTCY.

